{"lemma":"أَزَلُ","slug":"أَزَلُ","root":"#.ز.ل","root_slug":"_-ز-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ز-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَزَلُ","root":"زلل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n679","n682","n683","n684","n685","n17967"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"eternity (having no beginning to its existence)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔa.zal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n679","headword_ar":"اَزَلَ","root":"Azl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azolN","text_ar":"اَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became in a state of straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrowness, and suffering from dearth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [See also the pass. form of the verb here following; and see 5.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azalahu","text_ar":"اَزَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (K,) and so the inf. n., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He confined, restricted, restrained, withheld, debarred, hindered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevented, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,* TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitened him; in consequence of distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adversity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shortened his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tether,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then left him to pasture at pleasure"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K, [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~abahu","text_ar":"شَيَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~abahu","text_ar":"سَيَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaluwA maAlahumo","text_ar":"اَزَلُوا مَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amowaAlahumo","text_ar":"اَمْوَالَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. as above, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They confined, restricted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"debarred, their cattle from the place of pasturage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"send, them forth thereto,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dearth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sterility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-  It is said in a trad. respecting Ed-Dejjál, and his besieging the Muslims in Beytel-Makdis, [or Jerusalem,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayuw^ozaluwna A^azolFA $adiydFA","text_ar":"فَيُوْزَلُونَ اَزْلًا شَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they will be straitened with a vehement straitening."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uzila Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"اُزِلَ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people suffered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were afflicted with, drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n682","headword_ar":"اَزْلٌ","root":"Azl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Straitness; distress; difficulty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,* K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence of might,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of strength, in war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight; of courage, valour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of punishment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apu baA^osK","text_ar":"شِدَّةُ بَاْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  It is also used as an epithet, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strait; narrow; confined."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 339.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n683","headword_ar":"اـِزْلٌ","root":"Azl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) because of its distressing character. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falsehood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaa- koob, S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n684","headword_ar":"اَزَلٌ","root":"Azl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidamN","text_ar":"قِدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eternity, with respect to past time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"considered retrospectively; existence from eternity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancientness"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is without beginning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance of existence in decreed times interminable in respect of the past;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the continuance of existence in decreed times interminable in respect of the future; (KT;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which has no extremity in its beginning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidamN","text_ar":"قِدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which has no extremity in its latter part; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaA='N","text_ar":"بَقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existence without any beginning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 31:) said to be from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yazalo","text_ar":"لَمْ يَزَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“he, or it, has not ceased” to be &c.; i. e. “has ever” been &c. (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaliY~N","text_ar":"اَزَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]: or, accord. to some, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azolN","text_ar":"اَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “narrowness;” because the intellect is prevented by its narrowness from perceiving its beginning: (MF:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Azl","text_ar":"ازل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of which the mind is prevented by its narrowness from determining the limit of the beginning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azolN","text_ar":"اَزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “narrowness;”; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abd","text_ar":"ابد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name for that of which the mind shrinks from, or shuns, the determining the limit of the end; from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the act of “shrinking” from a thing, or “shunning” it. (Kull pp. 30 and 31.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna fiY AlA^azali qaAdirFA EaAlimFA","text_ar":"كَانَ فِى الاَزَلِ قَادِرًا عَالِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has been, ever, powerful, knowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azala AlA=zaAli","text_ar":"اَزَلَ الا=زَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"During the space, without beginning, of all past times;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ever, in all past times;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA=baAdi","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الا=بَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; said to be no evidence of the use of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=zaAlN","text_ar":"ا=زَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azalN","text_ar":"اَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a general way by the Arabs of the classical ages, as it is here added merely as a corroborative. (MF in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abd","text_ar":"ابد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azaliY~N","text_ar":"اَزَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n685","headword_ar":"اَزِلٌ","root":"Azl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=zilN","text_ar":"ا=زِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17967","headword_ar":"اَزَلُّ","root":"zl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zulozulN","text_ar":"زُلْزُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of flesh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haunches:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little flesh in the posteriors and thighs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having small buttocks sticking together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosaHu","text_ar":"اَرْسَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) in the copies of the K, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aj~u","text_ar":"اَشَجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or it signifies one who is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arosaH","text_ar":"اَرْسَح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose waist-wrapper will not retain its hold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zal~aA='u","text_ar":"زَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) applied to a woman;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasoHaA='u","text_ar":"رَسْحَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no buttock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zul~N","text_ar":"زُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imoEu AlA^azal~u","text_ar":"السِّمْعُ الاَزَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wolf that has little flesh in the rump and thighs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iy^obu","text_ar":"الذِّيْبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^arosaHu","text_ar":"الاَرْسَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iy^obN A^arosaHu","text_ar":"ذِيْبٌ اَرْسَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"begotten between the wolf and the she-hyena;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K; [the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAlxif~apu wAlqitAlu wAl$~ar~u","text_ar":"والخِفَّةُ والقِتالُ والشَّرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"here immediately following in the CK should be erased; their proper place being in the second of the lines below in that edition, where they are again inserted; as observed by Freytag;]) and this epithet ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAzl~","text_ar":"الازلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is inseparable: (S:) or, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^azal~u","text_ar":"الاَزَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"primarily signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the small in the buttock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and as an epithet applied to the wolf,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is said to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zal~a","text_ar":"زَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ he ran. ” (TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^asomaEu mina Als~imoEi","text_ar":"هُوَ اَسْمَعُ مِنَ السِّمْعِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^azal~i","text_ar":"الاَزَلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is more quick of hearing than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is lean in the rump and thighs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than the light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN zal~aA='u","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ زَلَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow from which the arrow slips, by reason of the rapidity with which it goes forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["AA","S","K","TA"]}]}}